race.comment: STEEL MOVE (2) missed a whisker at Seymour and followed with a 1.6L defeat as a short-priced favourite over 1447m at Geelong. Raced well in town the three prior and drops back to a shorter sprint today with the blinkers applied for the first time. John Allen rides from a handy gate, and the gelding looks well placed. MEISHO (11) was prominent at the corner and ran a much better race last start when narrowly beaten at Kilmore over this trip. An improver with strong prospects. CAROLINA BREEZE (9) resumes and has shown plenty in both race starts. Placed in a recent Flemington jumpout and won't have to be much improved to feature. BAY OF ZEA (8) presents third up off two solid efforts at Morphettville. She is still well shy of her best and will position forward from a handy barrier. Freshened and has to be considered.
